<br>
Back to Thunder of Karana, Verant could have changed a thousand different things on it to make it not so overpowering but still useful.  Goldbeard and I were testing this spell in Hall of Training the night before the change.  With every mob tishaned and malo'd, I got 2 out of 7 to stick while Goldy got 3 out 9 I think.  We probably could have gotten more to stick if we had a bard to occ, but we didnt.  Goldy even casted one on Dozekar and immediately died on aggro. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   When it stuck, the spell was extremely powerful, but changing it to a 100-mana sieve with 18 sec recast time makes it completely useless.   Here are some suggestions on what they could have changed:<br>
<br>
1) double the recast time on the spell so it take 6 paladins to complete the cycle instead of 3.<br>
<br>
2) increased the save check against the spell.  ToK checks at MR+15, if they increased it to MR+40 or MR+50, the chance of it landing would greatly decrease.  Occlusion decrease MR by 40, so if you increase the check by 25 to 35, then you would get about the same number I got, 2 out of 7.<br>
<br>
3) set a lvl ceiling of what is immune to the spell.  Make it so everything above lvl 63 is immune to the spell.  That way regular mobs in ToV are not immune to the spell while most dragons are.  If Verant can set a ceiling on what lvl can attack Naggy and Vox, then they can obviously set this cap.<br>
<br>
Olvan Anvildawn<br>
